Investec Is Said to Hire Five Banks For a $120 Million Two-Year Term Loan

-- B y   K a t r i n a   N i c h o l a s
-- 
2011-07-28T02:05:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/investec-is-said-to-hire-five-banks-for-120-million-two-year-term-loan.html
Investec Plc. (INVP) , which owns a private
banking business and money manager that operates in South
Africa, Australia and the U.K., hired five banks to help it
borrow $120 million in a two-year term loan, according to a
person familiar with the matter.  The company is offering margin and fees for a so-called top
level all-in payment of 195 basis points more than the London
interbank offered rate, the person said, asking not to be
identified as details are private.  Australia & New Zealand Banking Group Ltd. (ANZ) ,  China
Construction Bank Corp. (939) ,  State Bank of India (SBIN) , Standard Chartered
Plc and Bank of China Ltd. will help arrange the facility, the
person said. Investec has an option to increase the size of the
facility, depending on demand, and syndication is expected to
close in mid September, the person said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Katrina Nicholas at 
 knicholas2@bloomberg.net  